<p>The severity of a ligament tear can vary widely, classified into three grades: Grade I (mild), where the ligament is stretched but not torn; Grade II (moderate), involving a partial tear; and Grade III (severe), where the ligament is completely torn. A thorough evaluation by a healthcare professional, often involving a physical examination and imaging studies like MRI, is crucial to determine the extent of the injury and the appropriate treatment plan.</p>

