<p>The process of plaster application typically begins with a thorough evaluation of the fracture by a healthcare professional. After confirming the fracture type and location through imaging studies such as X-rays, the area is prepared for casting. The skin is often cleaned, and a soft padding material may be applied to protect the skin from direct contact with the plaster. This padding helps to absorb sweat and reduce discomfort while wearing the cast.</p>

