<p>Symptoms of tennis elbow typically include pain and tenderness on the outside of the elbow, which may radiate down the forearm. Patients often report difficulty with gripping objects, lifting items, or performing simple tasks like turning a doorknob. The pain may be exacerbated by specific movements, and individuals may notice stiffness or weakness in the affected arm. Early diagnosis and treatment are crucial to prevent the condition from becoming chronic.</p>

