<p>Initial management for tennis elbow often involves conservative measures, including rest, ice application, nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), and physical therapy. Physical therapy may focus on strengthening and stretching exercises to improve flexibility and reduce strain on the elbow. In some cases, corticosteroid injections may be used to alleviate pain and inflammation. If conservative treatments fail to provide relief after several months, more invasive options, such as shockwave therapy or surgery, may be considered.</p>

